  "grammarNote": {
    "title": "The Future: aller + infinitive",
    "explanation": "Avril va agir maintenant. — she IS GOING TO act. The pattern va + [infinitive verb] describes a near future action.\n\nNotice: Papa a envoyé (past — he sent) vs. Avril va agir (future — she will act). Past uses a + [-é], future uses va + [infinitive].\n\nRe-read and find every va + [verb]. What is about to happen?"
